<HEADLINE>
JUSTICE DOESN'T RISE FROM ASHES
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By E.J. MONTINI  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Fire gets our attention. All heat and light. But then the flames
subside and the smoke dissipates. The em bers cool. Ashes crumble
to dust and scatter in the wind. And we forget.
</P>
<P>
   The name Jermaine ``J.R.'' Miguel Jr. means nothing.
