</P>
<P>
   She worries about her other children, who don't receive the
attention she used to give them, and which they deserve, be cause
of all she must do for J.R.
</P>
<P>
   She worries about her burned son's ability to overcome all he's
been through and lead a normal life.
</P>
<P>
   She worries that the same thing could happen to another family.
</P>
<P>
   She worries, because she understands that whatever heat and
light another newspaper article may bring to the trag edy of her
son, it won't last.
</P>
<P>
   The glow subsides. The warmth cools. The paper crumbles to dust
and scatters in the wind. And we ask, J.R. who? &QL;
</P>
