<P>
   &UR; IN SEARCH OF THE ELUSIVE MEGAPLUME &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; FOUR COLOR SLIDES ARE AVAILABLE FREE &QL; 
 &UR; (1,100 words with a 200-word sidebar) &QL; 
 &UR; By JOSH FISCHMAN &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Imagine underwater volcanoes that erupt with giant twisting
plumes filled with microbes and other life that spin dervishly like
aquatic hurricanes. Welcome to the strange, almost completely
unknown life of undersea eruptions and what oceanographers are
beginning to learn about theses Vesuvians of the deep.
</P>
<P>
   slugged: BC-UNDERSTANDING-MEGAPLUMES-NYTSF. Sent to category
codes ``a'' general news and ``l'' lifestyle news.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENVIRONMENTAL MYTHS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; THREE COLOR ILLUSTRATIONS ARE AVAILABLE FREE &QL; 
 &UR; (600 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By THE EDITORS OF DISCOVER &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   The editors of Discover magazine set the record straight on a
spectrum of erroneous environmental assumptions, from the primary
source of U.S. energy (70 percent is derived from coal and other
fossil fuels) to the primary culprit responsible for oil pollution
(autos and boats _ not tankers). Learn the direct cause of damaging
environmental effects as well as what, if anything, is being done
to safeguard our national forest and bottled water. What you don't
know may surprise you.
</P>
<P>
   slugged: BC-ENVIRONMENTAL-MYTHS-NYTSF. Sent to category codes
``a'' general news and ``l'' lifestyle news.
</P>
<P>
   Both stories are also available in Spanish.
