<P>
   GOTH-BALL _ Fashion editor Cara Anna has gone to the Goth Ball
at local nightclub. (Ana, Palm Beach Post). 20.
</P>
<P>
   FASHION-CAPRIPANTS _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Shins are in. Their
moment in the fashion sun comes courtesy of capris, cropped pants
and clamdiggers _ all those britches hitched up at the hem. They,
along with pedal pushers and toreadors, are the latest style to be
regurgitated here at century's close. Fashion's capricious finger
now points back to the '50s and early '60s. ``It's the end of the
millennium, and we're revisiting our favorite times,'' says Michele
Weston, fashion and style director of Mode magazine. ``And weren't
the '50s a wonderful time to be around?'' (Sturrock, Palm Beach
Post) MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   FASHION-KIDS _ WACO, Texas _ It's hard to miss the eye-stopping
colors and styles of kids' clothes for spring. Young girls'
clothing aisles are spattered with the pinkest of pinks, opulent
oranges, vibrant violets and brilliant blues. ``They're definitely
wanting brights,'' said Jan Koskela, who works at Kid's Korner
clothing store at Doc and Laddy's. (Mays, Waco Tribune-Herald).
MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   FASHION-BOOKER _ He was once at the design helm of the oldest
couture house in the world. Now on his own with a brand-new
collection with his name on the label, Hylan Booker has emerged as
a fresh and creative force in evening wear. (Janjigian, Palm Beach
Daily News). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   HOME &AMP; GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   LEEMAY-COLUMN _ Mother and daughter square off in a fierce
digging, planting, watering and pruning contest that will be
decided next summer. Both are first-time gardeners, but this war in
LA (lower Atlanta) has high stakes, not to mention longtime
bragging rights. (May, Atlanta Journal-Constituion). WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   PROS-HOWTHEYLIVE _ One in a continuing series on how
professional designers live. Atlanta interior designer Bill Stewart
has a passion for all things '50s. His 1951 ranch house is a
perfect backdrop for his collection of post-war knickknacks.
(Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
