   CD REVIEWS _ On his first new album in seven years, Tom Waits
fancies himself a scarecrow: a kind of '40s film noir scarecrow,
from whose grimy black suit-coat tumbles a whiskey bottle, a big
soup bone, a pocket watch, a post horn and a sheet of music. Also,
Vonda Shepard. (Staff, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   KENNYCHESNEY _ A feature on country artist Kenny Chesney.
Chesney was just one of the new guys with hats whose career was
going nowhere _ until his latest single, ``How Forever Feels,'' hit
the charts. The uptempo ditty has been No. 1 on country charts for
five straight weeks. With fact box. (MLongino, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS
</P>
<P>
   SKUBE-ON-BOOKS _ Of all sports, stock-car racing is the one
whose appeal is hardest to explain. In Formula One racing, at least
there's an element of artistry, cars quick as cockroaches darting
now left, now right. But a Chevy Monte Carlo, garishly bedecked
with what amounts to billboards for a fleet of sponsors, roaring
'round and 'round an oval? (Skube, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
25.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: EMBARGOED UNTIL SUNDAY, MAY 2
</P>
