called the next Patricia Cornwell, has signed a high six-figure
deal for a series about a rural Georgia coroner; Emory professor Ha
Jin and Georgia State professor David Bottoms have won Guggenheims;
Don DeLillo has won the prestigious Jerusalem Prize; Whoopi
Goldberg and Rosie O'Donnell help launch ``Get Caught Reading''
campaign. (O'Briant, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-HOMEDEPOT _ It's bagels with Bernie at Chapter 11 bookstore
in Atlanta. Bernie Marcus signs his tell-all book, ``Built From
Scratch: How a Couple of Regular Guys Grew the Home Depot from
Nothing to $30 Billion.'' It's a real back-slapping, macho look the
company's early days. Roush's book, ``Inside Home Depot'' hit the
shelves at the same time. If you like cussin' and fussin', stick
with Bernie's. WITH PHOTO. MOVED WEDNESDAY.
</P>
<P>
   MONICA-BOOKSIGNING _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ She's been dumped
by a president, deposed by a special prosecutor and betrayed by her
best friend. But Monica Lewinsky can still unleash a smile to
outshine a paparazzi's flash. According to the famous First Intern,
Clinton was attracted to her bubbly personality. To the way, he
supposedly told her, that she lit up a room. So I drove to her book
signing in Fort Lauderdale not to cluck or chide or talk politics
or morality or other Big Issues. I went solely to check out the
charmisa factor; her ``wattage,'' if you will. Does she burn
brightly enough to light up a room? Or does she unleash barely
enough amps to power an electric toothbrush? (Sturrock, Palm Beach
Post) MOVED.
</P>
