<P>
   TRAVEL-ECUADOR _ QUITO, Ecuador _ Like most Latin American
capitals, there are two Quitos: the modern might-as-well-be
Nashville city of 1.5 million and the Spanish colonial ``Old
City,'' a congested web of narrow cobblestone streets and
confectionary-colored buildings that open on to enormous plazas and
spectacular churches. (Schemmel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution
freelancer; not for use by NYTNS clients) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
