<P>
   MONICA-BOOKSIGNING _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ She's been dumped
by a president, deposed by a special prosecutor and betrayed by her
best friend. But Monica Lewinsky can still unleash a smile to
outshine a paparazzi's flash. According to the famous First Intern,
Clinton was attracted to her bubbly personality. To the way, he
supposedly told her, that she lit up a room. So I drove to her book
signing in Fort Lauderdale not to cluck or chide or talk politics
or morality or other Big Issues. I went solely to check out the
charmisa factor; her ``wattage,'' if you will. Does she burn
brightly enough to light up a room? Or does she unleash barely
enough amps to power an electric toothbrush? (Sturrock, Palm Beach
Post) MOVED.
