<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Sweeps week, Frasier rips Dr. Laura
 &HT;    By Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Calling Dr. Laura. ``Frasier'' has your number.
</P>
<P>
   The controversial radio shrink Dr. Laura Schlesinger, known for
her stern judgments (and those Internet photos!), gets ripped
stem-to-stern tonight to kick off May sweeps.
</P>
<P>
   The always-glorious Christine Baranski, late of ``Cybill,''
guests as Dr. Nora Fairchild, an ill-advised addition to Frasier
Crane's radio station. When being interviewed for the job she's as
oily as bad Caesar salad, but once she gets behind the mike, she
turns into an avenging devil.
</P>
<P>
   ``Keep your knees together!'' Dr. Nora barks at one woman.
``Staple 'em!'' Another, who's having a problem with her mother, is
told the lady is ``a tumor ... a toxic harpy!''
</P>
<P>
   Frasier (Kelsey Grammer) unable to tame the shrew, uncovers her
spotty past: two divorces, an affair with a married man, and her
Achilles' heel: her own mother. Enter Piper Laurie, putting a new
spin on the hellion mom she played in ``Carrie.''
</P>
<P>
   Although ``Frasier,'' the alpha-sitcom of the Emmy Awards, is
not known for parodies or issue-wrestling, folks who find the good
doctor intolerant and obnoxious will be whooping their way through
this dig.
</P>
<P>
   ``Frasier''
</P>
<P>
   9 tonight on NBC
</P>
<P>
   Grade: A-
</P>
<P>
   Phil Kloer writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
