<HEADLINE>
HOW MUCH TROUBLE IS THAT DOGGIE IN THE MOVIE? A LOT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: What kind of small dog is in the film ``As Good As It Gets''?
My wife wants one for Mother's Day.
</P>
<P>
   _ B.G., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Verdell was played by six Brussels Griffons, a rare European
breed that has become popular since the movie's release.
</P>
<P>
   The National Brussels Griffon Club reports an ``astounding''
increase in people wanting one of the dogs. ``The Brussels Griffon,
although enormously charming and endearing, has never before been a
popular breed,'' the club states on its World Wide Web site.
``There are some very good reasons for this fact.''
</P>
<P>
   The club warns that some of the dogs are not suited for a house
with children and can be difficult to reliably house-train.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is a very hard time for someone new to the breed to find
a high-quality, sound puppy,'' the group advises. ``The movie has
been as bad as it gets for our breed.''
</P>
<P>
   For more information on the club and breeders, write to Denise
Brusseau, 5921 159th Lane N.W., Anoka, MN 55303-4169, or visit the
club's Web site at www.geocities.com/Heartland/Pointe/7519.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Help settle a dispute: Did Melissa Gilbert and Rosie
O'Donnell star together in a sitcom four years ago that only lasted
one season?
</P>
<P>
   _ L.W., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Gilbert and O'Donnell were co-stars in ``Stand By Your Man,''
a U.S. remake of the British series ``Birds of a Feather.'' They
played sisters who moved in together after their husbands were
jailed for armed robbery.
</P>
<P>
   The sitcom aired briefly on Fox during spring 1992. ``It got
canceled because the Richard Simmons Deal-A-Meal program got higher
ratings,'' O'Donnell told ``Entertainment Weekly.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to Drew Barrymore?
</P>
<P>
   _ W.A.M., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Barrymore in care of Creative Artists Agency, 9830
Wilshire Blvd., Beverly Hills, CA 90212.
</P>
<P>
   The 24-year-old actor is both performer and executive producer
of the current film ``Never Been Kissed.'' She will appear next
year in a ``Charlie's Angels'' movie.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
