   CONGRESS-KOSOVO (Washington) _ After the House handed President
Clinton two setbacks for his policy in the Balkans, we weigh the
outlook in the Senate for measures to support the military action
against Yugoslavia. By GREG McDONALD.
</P>
<P>
   ANTHRAX-VACCINE-SAFETY (Washington) _ The General Accounting
Office says it cannot determine the safety or effectiveness of the
controversial anthrax vaccine being administered to U.S. armed
forces. The GAO, Congress' main investigative arm, says the vaccine
hasn't been studied enough to make such a determination. But the
Food and Drug Administration, which licenses the vaccine, and the
Pentagon say the vaccine is safe, effective and necessary to
protect U.S. forces against the deadly anthrax disease. By JENNIFER
CORBETT DOOREN.
</P>
