<SLUG> BC-DOGS-T-SHIRTS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DOG T-SHIRTS GIVE BALL FANS PAWS _ AND SMILES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SANDY GUERRA-CLINE 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Some combinations are just naturals:
baseball and kids, dogs and kids, T-shirts with dogs playing
baseball on them and kids.
</P>
<P>
   At least it seemed a natural to C.W. ``Dunk'' Duncan, owner of
Fort Worth's Arc Park, a family sports park where baseball, dogs
and kids often collide. Last year, Duncan decided his idea had legs
_ albeit shaggy ones _ and Sportsdawgz was born.
</P>
<P>
   Duncan plans to design an entire team of T-shirts. For now,
Sportsdawgz is offering Fetch, a golden retriever outfielder;
Slugger, an English bulldog power hitter; and Roc, a Rottweiler, at
catcher. The word is, Ivan Rodriguez of the Texas Rangers loves his
``dawg'' shirt.
</P>
<P>
   The artwork is done by Fort Worth artist Dennis Farris. Coming
soon: Stretch, Heater, Flip, Chase, Shorty, Race, Digger and Cappy,
the team manager.
</P>
<P>
   Duncan is donating a portion of the T-shirt sales to Alliance
for Children. He serves on the local board of the national,
nonprofit group, which works with victims of child abuse and has
centers in Fort Worth, Northeast Tarrant County and Arlington.
</P>
<P>
   ``The basic message of Sportsdawgz is to play the game for no
other reason than to have fun and be good sports,'' said Duncan.
``If we can help Alliance for Children toward that end, then so
much the better.''
</P>
<P>
   T-shirts can be ordered by calling Arc Park at 834-8888 or on
the Web at www.sportsdawgz.com. C.R. Paws, 4211 S. Cooper St. in
Arlington, also carries them. Youth-size shirts are $14.50,
adult-size $15.50 and XXL $17.50.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
