<P>
   KOSOVO-INFRASTRUCTURE (Belgrade, Yugoslavia) _ NATO's five-week
air campaign against Yugoslavia's military, intended to change
President Slobodan Milosevic's policies toward the southern Serb
province of Kosovo, is also destroying Yugoslavia's civilian
industrial capacity and infrastructure, including its highway, rail
and communications networks. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-CONGRESS (Washington) _ House Republicans moved Thursday
to add billions to the bill for NATO's air war against Serbia
Thursday, the day after they denied President Clinton political
support for fighting it. By Tim Weiner.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-CONGRESS-ASSESS (Washington) _ For Congress, or even one
house of Congress, to refuse to endorse current combat missions is
about as unusual as Congress keeping pork out of an urgent spending
bill. But the House is taking the first of those untrodden paths
even as it takes its customary route on the second. A news
analysis. By Adam Clymer.
</P>
