   COXNET FOCUS PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDs: CoxNet's FOCUS page for the week of April 30 is available.
The page is a profile of Vice President Al Gore. The story is a
70-inch verison of a longer piece that is on the Sunday budget and
has moved on the wire. The story was written by Palm Beach Post
reporter Paul Reid.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FOCUS 0430 GORE _ Now is Al Gore's time to tell us who he
is. The vice president says he has a compelling vision of where we
want to go as a nation, how we can get there and how we can live
better lives when we arrive. For the next 18 months, Gore will tell
us why he wants to be president: ``Because I want to do the job _
you have to want it _ because I can do the job, because I love my
country and am grateful for the chance to lead this country ... I
thank God for Tipper's love. The love we share will see us through.
We're ready. I'm ready. I'm excited.'' (Reid, Palm Beach Post) Art
includes 3 color photographs -- Gore greeting supporters, Gore
talking to civic group and Gore and wife Tipper relaxing on Air
Force 2.
