<P>
   COKE _ Coca-Cola Chairman M. Douglas Ivester told employees that
while the racial discrimination suit against the company has
``significant errors of fact,'' he is taking it ``very seriously.''
``I have spent time this week with senior African-American
associates of the company to get their insights and opinions on the
circumstances that have led to this serious litigation,'' Ivester
said in the e-mail to some 9,000 U.S. employees. (Unger, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
