   NH-TAX (Concord, N.H.) _ N.H. Legislature passes an $825 million
patchwork of taxes, which Gov. Jeanne Shaheen immediately signs
into law, ending the state's school-funding crisis. By Jill
Zuckman. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   PATRIOTS-STADIUM (Boston) _ Patriots owner Robert Kraft holds a
crucial session with his Hartford stadium consultants, then is
expected to meet with Connecticut Governor John G. Rowland. By Meg
Vaillancourt. 1200 words. (a and s coding)
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; UNITARIAN-SCOUTS (Undated) _ Unitarian Universalist
Association and the Boy Scouts of America resolve a dispute
involving the church's liberal stance on homosexuality and
religious awards it gives to scouts who are Unitarians. By Diego
Ribadeneira. 500 words.
</P>
<P>
   SHOOTING (Littleton, Colo.) _ Isaiah Shoels is buried amid hymns
from popular recording artists and calls for racial unity. By Ellen
O'Brien. 1000 words.
</P>
