   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   WAGES-SLOW (Undated) _ Americans' wages rose in the first
quarter at their slowest pace in years, the government reports,
despite what may be the tightest job market in years. By Kimberly
Blanton. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   LOTUS-PAPOWS (Undated) _ Lotus says it will stand behind its
CEO, Jeff Papows, in the face of allegations that he has fabricated
details of his military service record and educational background.
By Hiawatha Bray. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   COVANCE-PAREXEL (Undated) _ Drug-development company Parexel is
acquired for $827 million by one of its major competitors, Covance
Inc. of Princeton, N.J., creating the world's largest
drug-development firm. By Alex Pham. 600 words.
</P>
