<TEXT>
<P>
   The New York Times plans 3 pages of stories, photos and graphics
on the continuing crisis in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-YUGO-ARMY (Washington) _ By triggering a ``rally around
the flag'' effect in Serbia, five weeks of NATO bombing has had the
unintended and unwanted result of uniting the Yugoslav army around
the defense of its country, according to senior NATO and American
officials. By Steven Lee Myers.
</P>
<P>
   With:
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-INFRASTRUCTURE (Belgrade, Yugoslavia) _ NATO's five-week
air campaign against Yugoslavia's military, intended to change
President Slobodan Milosevic's policies toward the southern Serb
province of Kosovo, is destroying Yugoslavia's civilian industrial
capacity and infrastructure, including its highway, rail and
communications networks. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-CONGRESS (Washington) _ House Republicans moved Thursday
to add billions to the bill for NATO's air war against Serbia
Thursday, the day after they denied President Clinton political
support for fighting it. By Tim Weiner.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-CONGRESS-ASSESS (Washington) _ News Analysis: For
Congress, or even one house of Congress, to refuse to endorse
current combat missions is about as unusual as Congress keeping
pork out of an urgent spending bill. But the House is taking the
first of those untrodden paths even as it takes its customary route
on the second. By Adam Clymer.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-DIPLO (Berlin) _ A diplomatic roundup: Germany's
Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder sees ``movement toward a political
solution'' after meeting Viktor Chernomyrdin, the special Russian
envoy; Strobe Talbott, the deputy secretary of state, talks tough
in Brussels. By Roger Cohen.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Brussels) _ NATO missile hits a suburb of Sofia,
Bulgaria's capital, 30 miles from Yugoslavia. No one hurt. Allied
bombers pound Montenegro, to get Yugoslav planes, and hit Slobodan
Milosevic's home town for first time. By Craig R. Whitney.
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-MACEDONIA (Dateline to kum) _ Five refugees, crossing
from Kosovo into Macedonia, are killed by a land mine. By Barry
Bearak.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-JACKSON (Undated) _ Developments on Jesse Jackson's trip
to Belgrade. By Susan Sachs.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-TRIBUNAL (Undated) _ Developments at the international
war crimes tribunal.
</P>
