   And Rep. Cynthia McKinney, D-Ga., who also voted against the air
war, joined two Democratic colleagues in a ``teach-in'' for a
diplomatic solution. ``Our bombing campaign has only resulted in
the displacement of millions of Kosovars and the destruction of
some buildings, but no peace,'' she said Thursday on Capitol Hill.
</P>
<P>
   Other Democrats reacted bitterly to the upset votes in the
House. Rep. Jim McDermott, D-Wash., complained that the House was
abandoning the troops. But then, noting that Congress was planning
to pass funding for the Balkan air war that the House has just
repudiated, McDermott said he felt as if he were in Alice's
``Wonderland.''
</P>
<P>
   ``This place is getting curiouser and curiouser,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
