<P>
   ECON-REPORT (Washington) _ Despite declining unemployment and a
shortage of workers in some industries, wage and benefit increases
slowed markedly in the first three months of the year, the
government reported Thursday. The employment cost index, the
government's measure for tracking changes in compensation costs,
rose 0.4 percent in the first quarter, the smallest increase on
record. The small rise was about half of what economists had
expected and is the strongest sign yet that inflationary pressures
remain muted. By Richard W. Stevenson. With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Display)
</P>
<P>
   CLUB-MED (Cancun, Mexico) _ Club Med, the Paris-based company
credited with originating the ``all-inclusive'' vacation, fell on
hard financial times through much of this decade. But Club Med is
now combating its old reputation as a dated swingers' paradise by
offering cultural and literary forums and by renovating its
villages. Attendance is rising, and analysts say Club Med is
finally heading in the right direction. By Edwin McDowell. With
graphic.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.) &QL;
</P>
