</P>
<P>
   REALESTATE-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ Until now, Warren Buffett's
best-known real estate gamble was on a bank. Now, the Omaha
billionaire is betting on real estate again. And investors are left
to wonder if he has correctly spotted the bottom _ this time in
real estate stocks _ or if he is he early again. By Richard A.
Oppel Jr. With graphic.
</P>
<P>
   (Bottom Center)
</P>
<P>
   HEDGE-FUNDS (Undated) _ Hedge fund managers, who half a year ago
were beside themselves that regulators might clamp down on their
freewheeling partnerships in the wake of Long-Term Capital
Management's near collapse, are breathing easier. A long-awaited
government report Thursday did not propose, for now, any direct
regulation of hedge funds. By Richard A. Oppel Jr.
</P>
