and personalities that make business more than a dollars and cents
proposition.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-WORLD-FARBEN (Frankfurt, Germany) _ This will be a new
biweekly feature on the business world. This week: A look at the
German chemical company, I.G. Farben, which has been around since
the Nazi regime. By Edmund L. Andrews.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-CULTURE (Undated) _ The Culture of Money column, on the
emblematic transaction of our times, the auction. By Daniel Akst.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-ECON-COLUMN (Undated) _ The Economic View column. By David
E. Sanger.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-DIARY (Undated) _ Short items on surveys, research and new
consumer products.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-DESALINATON-PLANTS (Undated) _ Turning salt water into fresh
has for decades something you only considered doing in extremis,
because the process was balky and very expensive. But some new
breakthroughs in membrane technology &QL; 
may make desalination plants a more practical and common source of
fresh water, a potential boon to the companies that make and sell
them. By Claudia H. Deutsch.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-JAPAN-BANKS (Oakland, Calif.) _ Two Japanese bankers, Jun
Satoh and Eiichi Haruki, has come to United States to entice
institutional money managers to invest in Japan's huge mountain of
defaulted bank loans. By Andrea Adelson.
</P>
<P>
   With Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-TOTAL-FUNDS (Undated) _ Total Market Index funds are the
latest rage. &QL; 
Here is what you should know. By Robert D. Hershey Jr.
</P>
<P>
   With Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-COLUMN (Undated) _ Strategies column: Sector rotation. By
Mark Hulbert.
</P>
<P>
   With Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-INSIGHT-Q&AMP;A (Undated) _ A Q&AMP;A with a market insider. By
