<P>
   ABOUT-CARS-MINIVANS (Undated) _ I had not cared much for
minivans, preferring the handling of even a station wagon over a
box on wheels. Then I took a family trip in a Plymouth Grand
Voyager, hauled home a Christmas tree on the roof of a Toyota
Sienna and took some Cub Scouts camping in a Ford Windstar. Now I
have to concede there is no better way for adults or children to
make the long haul. By Leonard M. Apcar.
</P>
<P>
   With Photo.
</P>
<P>
   CAR-SMART-VAN-RANKINGS (Undated) _ Virtually every vehicle
manufacturer has the ergonomics of the minivan down pat.
Functionality, comfort and convenience, after all, are the point in
driving these dens on wheels. So determining which is the best must
now include some other factors. For convenience (and the safety of
children getting in or out on one-way streets), four doors have
become absolutely essential. Power-operated sliding doors win extra
credit from me. I appreciate extra horsepower, especially if it
doesn't push down the fuel economy, and nimble, car-like handling.
By Michelle Krebs.
</P>
