<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GETAWAY-FESTIVALS29-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Southern happenings
 &HT;    By Paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  Gay, Ga. _ Cotton Pickin' Country Fair Saturday and Sunday
includes arts, crafts and antiques, entertainment and county
cooking on the grounds of an old cotton-ginning complex.
706-538-6814.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Columbus, Ga. _ The Springer Opera House presents Alfred
Uhry's ``The Last Night of Ballyhoo'' Thursday-Sunday and May 6-8.
Tickets: 706-327-3688.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Tifton, Ga. _ The 19th annual Love Affair arts festival begins
Thursday with ``Music and More on Main Street,'' featuring jazz by
the Jim Newton Combo, folk-country-bluegrass by Three on a String
and clowning by Tomas Kubinek: Certified Lunatic and Master of the
Impossible. The event continues Friday, with a picnic and concert
featuring the Diamonds in Fullwood Park, and Saturday, with nonstop
entertainment, fine art, crafts and food. 912-386-3558.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Vidalia, Ga. _ The 22nd annual Vidalia Onion Festival Thursday
through May 2 opens with a Children's Parade and entertainment at
Southeastern Technical Institute and continues Friday with a street
dance. On Saturday and May 2, there will be an air show, carnival
rides, arts and crafts show, entertaining and lots of food.
912-538-8687.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Winchester, Va. _ The 72nd Annual Shenandoah Apple Blossom
Festival today through Sunday includes a parade, concerts,
carnival, circus, arts and crafts fair and athletic competitions.
1-800-230-2139.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Port Royal, S.C. _ The Spring Tour of Homes on Saturday
celebrates the 125th birthday of the small Beaufort County town.
Includes a tour of historic homes and gardens, Civil War
re-enactors, an exhibit of antique automobiles, arts and crafts
show and sale, parade and entertainment. 843-524-4333.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  St. Augustine, Ga. _ The fourth annual Gamble Rogers Folk
Festival Friday through May 2 at the St. Augustine Amphitheater
features Arlo Guthrie, Robin and Linda Williams, top acoustic
musicians, storytelling, finger-style guitar competition,
workshops, demonstrations, jamming, dance, food, folk art and
crafts. 904-471-1965.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Panama City Beach, Fla. _ The first ``Bike'N Beach Bash''
takes place at locations throughout the city today through Sunday.
Actor Mickey Jones, best known for his recurring role as
construction worker Pete Bilker on TV's ``Home Improvement,'' is
celebrity host for the event that features a vendor village, bands,
bikini contest, motorcycle shows and awards, including ``Best of
Show.'' 1-800-722-3224 or www.800pcbeach.com
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fernandina Beach, Fla. _ The 36th annual Isle of Eight Flags
Shrimp Festival Friday through Sunday is a celebration of seafood
and history with more than 350 fine arts, crafts and antiques
vendors, entertainment on two stages, a ``Fun Zone'' with games,
activities and food booths serving shrimp creations. Opening
ceremonies Friday night include a pirate invasion and fireworks.
904-261-0203.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Lake Buena Vista, Fla. _ The sixth annual Epcot International
Flower &AMP; Garden Festival continues through May 30. It features 90
Disney character topiaries, interactive garden-themed activities
for children, tips from Disney gardeners, workshops, seminars,
gardening techniques and displays and more. 407-824-4321.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Asheville, N.C. _ The 10th annual Spring Herb Festival at the
Western North Carolina Farmers Market is Friday through May 2. The
largest herb festival in the Southeast features herb products from
60 businesses, educational programs, garden displays and herbal
lunches. 828-689-5974.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Coastal Virginia _ The third annual Virginia Waterfront
International Arts Festival through May 9 includes renowned artists
from around the world performing in Norfolk, Williamsburg, Virginia
Beach, Gloucester, Hampton, Portsmouth, Chesapeake and Newport
News. Headliners include the Boys Choir of Harlem and the Russian
National Ballet. 757-664-6692 or www.virginiaartsfest.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ Paula Crouch Thrasher writes for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
