<HEADLINE>
FOREIGN BRIEFS 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   ISRAEL
</P>
<P>
   FUROR OVER SHAS TAPE: A videotape released by the ultra-Orthodox
Shas Party has caused a storm. In the tape, Shas leader Aryeh Deri,
who was recently sentenced on bribery charges, said the judicial
system had railroaded him because he is a Moroccan-born religious
Jew. Both confusing and offending many here, Deri compared his
treatment with that of John Demjanjuk, whose conviction as a Nazi
war criminal was overturned, and to that of Adolf Eichmann, a
convicted Nazi war criminal who was executed.
</P>
<P>
   _ By Deborah Sontag
</P>
<P>
   SPAIN
</P>
<P>
   BASQUE SEPARATIST DETAINED: Police arrested a convicted Basque
separatist rebel, Juan Carlos Estevez Paz, 29, immediately after
his expulsion from France, where he spent nearly five years in
prison for his role in a failed assassination plot against King
Juan Carlos in 1995 during a vacation by the king in Majorca. Four
other Basque rebels have also been convicted in the plot. Estevez
now faces other terrorism charges in Spain.
</P>
<P>
   _ By Al Goodman
</P>
