on board.``Noah's Ark'' is a shipwreck of a movie that might work
as a Sunday school diversion for 5-year-olds, but it isn't apt to
do much for anyone who has reached the age of reason. Like a bad
sermon, it's too long. Like a bad toupee, it's too obvious. Like a
bad Velveeta recipe, it's too cheesy.
