vehicle used to land on the moon, at the Smithsonian's Air and
Space Museum. museum is one of the most popular attractions in
Washington; as well as one of the most crowded. (Shana Raab/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) UNDATED -- April 29, 1999 -- VITAMIN-COCKTAIL, 4-29 -- A
burgeoning number of Americans are starting each day with vitamin
cocktails, a practice also known as stacking, in which a dozen or
more vitamins, herbals, minerals or food supplements are taken
together as a talisman against poor health. Recent surveys show
that more than half of the U.S. population uses dietary supplements
and spends nearly $10 billion on them annually. (Photo by Sherrie
Buzby/The Arizona Republic)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
