<SLUG> BC-BLOCK-REVENUE-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
H&AMP;R BLOCK ENJOYS `GOOD TAX SEASON' 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By GENE MEYER  
 c. 1997 The Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   H&AMP;R Block Inc. said Thursday that its U.S. tax service revenue
jumped 15 percent this season, to $1.5 billion, as more people
sought help because of changes in federal tax laws. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Block, based in Kansas City, also reported that it filed a
record 11 million electronic returns for clients and customers
between Jan. 1 and April 15, which is 18.2 percent more than a year
ago. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Overall, it was a good tax season for us,'' Frank L.
Salizzoni, the company's president and chief executive, said in a
statement released with the numbers. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``We believe changes to the tax code, like the new child tax and
education credits, combined with a more strategic marketing
campaign, drove additional clients to our offices,'' Salizzoni
said. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   More than 16.1 million clients, or 4.8 percent more than last
year, came to more than 8,900 U.S. tax service offices operated by
Block and its franchisees, the company said. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The average fee increased 9.7 percent to $92.57, about
two-thirds of which is because of the increased complexity of the
forms that taxpayers filed, the company said. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Block said it planned to release full results for the fiscal
year ending today around June 15. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
