<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-29 23:58 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8971 &Cx1f; tab-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-KIDS:HOROSCOPE-CLASSA     04-29 0689
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KIDS:HOROSCOPE-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
STAR STRUCK? CHECK OUT YOUR WEEK 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By Students SARABETH BALON and NICK FOREMAN 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Before finalizing your activities, take time to read the
following horoscope, which is a fun way to plan your week.
</P>
<P>
   TAURUS (April 20 - May 20): Lately, you are all about helping
others. Your work pays off with every smile you receive for your
hard work. Soon you will be presented with a charity project. Take
it on. It will be a challenge, but if you do not take charge, who
will?
</P>
<P>
   GEMINI (May 21 - June 20): A very extraordinary event will occur
this week accompanied by shocking news. You will like certain
aspects and dislike others, but all in all it will create a memory
that will last a lifetime. Do not overreact when petty things
bother you.
</P>
<P>
   CANCER (June 21 - July 22): You are becoming more and more
despondent. Wake up from the daze you have been in lately. Get back
in touch with what is important in your life. Re-evaluate the
things that matter to you.
</P>
<P>
   LEO (July 23 - Aug. 22): Busy, busy, busy! These days you find
yourself busy as a bee. It is important that you keep a planner
because it is impossible to keep up with all your due dates. If you
choose not to, you may find yourself in a sticky situation.
</P>
<P>
   VIRGO (Aug. 23 - Sept. 22): Last week you made people aware of
something special you possess. This week is your time to shine. Be
proud of your accomplishments. It is true that nobody likes a cocky
person, but truth also lies in the fact that you can be proud
without overdoing it.
</P>
<P>
   LIBRA (Sept. 23 - Oct. 22): Take a deep breath because your past
week has been a nightmare. You have a good friend who is watching
out for you this week. You will be in an awkward position later
this week and will not have time to thoroughly think the situation
out, so be quick on your feet.
</P>
<P>
   SCORPIO (Oct. 23 - Nov. 21): Be the regulator between your
friends. At this time of year, everybody gets a little edgy. When
your friends come to you, do not take sides. That could be a big
mistake, and you do not want to get into the middle of this; it
could get ugly. You will be given a bit of good news that has been
long in coming.
</P>
<P>
   SAGITTARIUS (Nov. 22 - Dec. 21): This week, lighten up a tad.
Your week will be somewhat boring unless you make it into something
special. When you put your mind to it, you can have all the fun in
the world. Do not necessarily plan it, because that takes away some
of the fun. Fly by the seat of your pants.
</P>
<P>
   CAPRICORN (Dec. 22 - Jan. 19): It is hard to tell when somebody
is lying to you and when he is telling the truth. In one respect,
you need to be able to trust your friends. At the same time, you
need to check into something that might be fishy. A truth may be
hidden in a bushel of lies.
</P>
<P>
   AQUARIUS (Jan. 20 - Feb. 18): A sudden rise in your social
activities will lead you to a new hottie. They will sweep you off
your feet and either continue to carry you or let you fall flat on
your face. You do not want to move too fast and assume that you
know exactly who they are. This one should be on the safe side, but
ask around before you get too wrapped up in them.
</P>
<P>
   PISCES (Feb. 19 - March 20): You might find yourself in a
relaxed and smooth atmosphere this week. It will be a confidence
boost when you realize how much you really mean to your friends and
family. A flagrant show of appreciation is coming your way. Many of
the things that you couldn't do before, you will now be able to do.
</P>
<P>
   ARIES (March 21 - April 19): Feeling exhausted? Are you plagued
with the nuisances of homework and housework? Do not expect a break
from the business of your life in the immediate future. Things are
growing strong, but who knows how long. It takes a big person to
ask for help.
</P>
